{{planes of existence}}
The '''physical plane''' (also known as a [[hyperplane]]), '''physical world''', or '''physical universe''', in [[emanation]]ist metaphysics such as are found in [[Neoplatonism]], [[Hermeticism]], [[Hinduism]] and [[Theosophy (Blavatskian)|Theosophy]], refers to the visible [[reality]] of [[space]] and [[time]], [[energy]] and [[matter]]: the physical universe in [[Occultism]] and [[esoteric cosmology]] is the lowest or [[density|densest]] of a series of [[Plane (cosmology)|planes of existence]] (hyperplanes that are said to be nested).

